<BaseLayout title="Founding Engineer - Careers - Sylience" description="Join Sylience as Founding Engineer and own Chord's technical execution.">
  <div class="job-header">
    <h1>Founding Engineer</h1>
    <p class="job-meta">Remote, US timezones preferred</p>
  </div>

  <h2>About Chord</h2>

  <section class="section">
    <p>
      Sylience, the company building Chord, is a public benefit corporation with the mission
      to improve reasoning and cooperation, enable broad participation in decision-making,
      foster human connection, and enhance human agency. Sylience closed its pre-seed round
      in January 2026 and is currently building out the founding team.
    </p>
  </section>

  <h2>About the role</h2>

  <section class="section">
    <p>
      As Founding Engineer, you'll be the primary owner of Chord's technical execution.
    </p>

    <h3>You will:</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>Ship and iterate quickly based on user feedback as Chord develops product-market fit.</li>
      <li>Collaborate closely with the CEO on product direction.</li>
      <li>Take the lead on key architectural decisions as Chord expands its customer base and extends its functionality.</li>
      <li>Combine existing best practices with new approaches to support novel human&ndash;AI and human&ndash;human collaboration patterns.</li>
      <li>Push the boundaries of what's possible using AI to accelerate product development while maintaining high standards.</li>
      <li>Help shape the engineering culture and mentor future hires as the team grows.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <h3>You may be a good fit if:</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>You have 7+ years experience building full-stack web applications.</li>
    <li>You move quickly and thrive in fast-paced iterative environments.</li>
    <li>You're an expert in modern web development architectures.</li>
    <li>You're proficient in both Python (FastAPI) and TypeScript (React/Next.js).</li>
    <li>You've been experimenting extensively with AI-assisted software development and you're continuously iterating on your workflow to increase your velocity.</li>
    <li>You believe the development of AI poses extremely important questions for humanity, and you're excited to improve our capability for making good collective decisions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>We don't expect candidates to have done everything, but we'd be excited if:</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>You've previously worked at a startup where you built a product from zero to one.</li>
    <li>You have strong design skills and have built exceptional user experiences.</li>
    <li>You have experience building your own AI agents or agentic workflows.</li>
    <li>You have experience with complex data architectures, including distributed systems, real-time data streams, and information retrieval.</li>
    <li>You've built desktop and/or mobile applications.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Compensation</h2>

  <section class="section">
    <p>
      <strong>Salary:</strong> $100,000&ndash;$150,000 USD depending on your cash vs equity
      preference, with a market-adjustment review at Series A.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Equity:</strong> 1&ndash;5% depending on experience and salary requirements.
      Negotiable for especially impressive candidates.
    </p>
  </section>

  <h2>Apply</h2>

  <section class="section">
    <p>
      Send your resume to <a href="mailto:careers@sylience.com">careers@sylience.com</a> with
      the subject line "Application for Founding Engineer role - [Your Name]".
    </p>
    <p>Optionally, please feel free to include 1&ndash;2 sentences in your email about any or all of:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Why you're interested in Chord;</li>
      <li>Why you think you'd be a good fit;</li>
      <li>Anything else you think we should know.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <p><a href="/careers">&larr; Back to all roles</a></p>
</BaseLayout>
